modules.description: This module models a damped spring system using a snapshot-based update function that computes position and velocity changes over time. It works with floating-point values and a snapshot record tracking position and velocity, using parameters like angular frequency and damping ratio to control spring behavior. Concrete use cases include simulating smooth animations, physics-based UI transitions, and dynamic motion control in games or interactive applications.

This module simulates damped spring systems using snapshot-based updates to compute position and velocity changes over time. It operates on floating-point values and maintains state through a snapshot record, incorporating parameters such as angular frequency and damping ratio to control motion dynamics. It enables tasks like animating smooth UI transitions, modeling physical systems, and implementing responsive game mechanics with precise motion control. Example usage includes calculating spring motion at fixed time intervals or adjusting damping to simulate different material behaviors.
